    //    If 'correct_consecutive_pairs' are already present, we save that many 'put' operations.
    //    So, (n-1 - correct_consecutive_pairs) 'put' operations are explicitly performed.
    // 2. Any existing nesting that is NOT part of the 1->2->...->n sequence must be undone.
