        // The parity of (x+y) changes to (x+dx+y+dy) mod 2.
        // (x+y) mod 2 vs (x+dx+y+dy) mod 2.
        // This is equivalent to (dx+dy) mod 2.
        // For diagonal moves (dx,dy) where dx,dy are non-zero: dx+dy can be 0 or 2 (e.g., 1+1, 1-1, -1+1, -1-1). So dx+dy is even.
        // For straight moves (dx,dy) where one is zero: dx+dy can be 1 or -1. So dx+dy is odd.
