        // If one of dx, dy is zero (straight move), dx+dy is odd. Parity of (x+y) is flipped.
        //
        // So, if we make `s` straight moves and `d` diagonal moves, total moves `k = s + d`.
        // The parity of (n+m) must be the same as the parity of `s`.
        // (abs_n + abs_m) % 2 == s % 2.
        //
        // We start at (0,0). After K moves, we are at (n,m).
